# Day 8 - Data Engineer vs Data Analyst vs Data Scientist vs ML Engineer

## Data Engineer

A Data Engineer builds and manages data pipelines.

Their main job is to collect, store, and organize data.

### Responsibilities

* Collect data
* Build data pipelines
* Manage databases
* Prepare data for analysis

## Data Analyst

A Data Analyst analyzes data and finds useful insights.

They help businesses make better decisions.

### Responsibilities

* Analyze data
* Create reports
* Build dashboards
* Find trends and patterns

## Data Scientist

A Data Scientist uses data to solve business problems.

They use statistics and Machine Learning to make predictions.

### Responsibilities

* Analyze complex data
* Build ML models
* Perform data visualization
* Generate business insights

## ML Engineer

An ML Engineer builds and deploys Machine Learning models.

They focus on making ML systems work in real applications.

### Responsibilities

* Train ML models
* Deploy models
* Optimize performance
* Monitor ML systems

## Difference

| Role           | Main Focus                       |
| -------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Data Engineer  | Data Collection and Storage      |
| Data Analyst   | Data Analysis and Reporting      |
| Data Scientist | Data Analysis and Prediction     |
| ML Engineer    | Building and Deploying ML Models |

## Workflow

Data Engineer → Data Analyst → Data Scientist → ML Engineer

## Important Points

* Data Engineers handle data infrastructure.
* Data Analysts find insights from data.
* Data Scientists build predictive models.
* ML Engineers deploy and maintain ML models.
* All roles are important in Data Science projects.

## One-Line Summary

Data Engineers manage data, Data Analysts analyze data, Data Scientists build predictive solutions, and ML Engineers deploy Machine Learning models.
